<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#6809e2422c882d2cca7f9652205b609c>.
<#6809e2422c882d2cca7f9652205b609c> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Create>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/865891bbcb49b10639e82cc95a7f6f32>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-12T06:33:27.800Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#6809e2422c882d2cca7f9652205b609c> {
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/865891bbcb49b10639e82cc95a7f6f32> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Chalmers University of Technology", "Cluster expansions"@en, "Neuroevolution potential"@en, "Machine-learned interatomic potential"@en, "Monte Carlo simulations"@en, "Surfaces"@en, "Surface segregation"@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2026-02-28T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2026-03-03T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Data and code supporting the paper \"Competing adsorption of H and CO on Pd-alloy surfaces: Mechanistic insight into the mitigating effect of Cu on CO poisoning\""@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__2882.
_:b0__2882 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/2bb7c9f1e64b03ce124e8b817866c0fb>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/865891bbcb49b10639e82cc95a7f6f32> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__5546.
_:b0__5546 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/ace44333b1a9307c7f1a7205e04f07cc>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/865891bbcb49b10639e82cc95a7f6f32> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE5564795598>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "This record contains machine-learned interatomic potential (MLIP) and cluster expansion (CE) models for the AuCuPd:CO,H system along with reference data from density functional theory (DFT) calculations. Technical details are provided in\n\nPernilla Ekborg-Tanner and Paul ErhartCompeting adsorption of H and CO on Pd-alloy surfaces: Mechanistic insight into the mitigating effect of Cu on CO poisoningdoi: https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.2603.00776\n\nMLIP models\n\nModels based on the neuroevolution potential (NEP) architecture are provided in the nep-*.txt files. The \"full\" model has been trained against all available data whereas the \"split\" models have been trained against a random selection of 90% structures from the available structures.\n\nModels based on the MACE architecture are provided in the MACE-*.model files.\n\nCE models\n\nModels are provided for (111), (110), and (100) surfaces in the *.ce files along with reference structures in the *.xyz files\n\nReference data\n\nReference data from DFT calculations is provided in the reference-structures.db file, which is a sqlite database generated using the ase package."@en;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#ec99add0a418ef45a9b06916f2ad9222>.
<#ec99add0a418ef45a9b06916f2ad9222> a <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#Create>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#object> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/8e59ec7812e594330c6b0fbb53afca01>;
    <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams#published> "2026-04-12T06:33:27.800Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>.
<#ec99add0a418ef45a9b06916f2ad9222> {
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/8e59ec7812e594330c6b0fbb53afca01> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Pain"@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2026-02-27T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2026-02-27T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Dataset related to sub-study one of the PainSMART-project (RCT-PROMs primary and secondary outcomes)."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/HEAL>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__9304.
_:b0__9304 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/6478831fed5847297af292691c8ffb9d>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/8e59ec7812e594330c6b0fbb53afca01> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/NON_PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021003096>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Data supporting the results of this study comprise patient reported outcome measures (PROMs) and baseline information used as covariates in adjusted models. \n\nData were collected for the two groups (PainSMART-group and Control Group) via online questionnaires at four time points: Baseline, follow-up 1 (24-72 hours pre-initial physiotherapy consultation), follow-up 2 (24 hours post-initial physiotherapy consultation) and follow-up 3 (three months post-baseline).\n\nThe following PROMs were collected:\n\nPrimary outcomes\n\n-    Average pain intensity in the last 24 hours (NRS-average pain, 0-10).\n\n-    Pain self-efficacy (Pain Self Efficacy Questionnaire, PSEQ-10, 0-60).\n\nSecondary outcomes\n\n-    Best pain intensity in the last 24 hours (NRS-best pain, 0-10).\n\n-    Worst pain intensity in the last 24 hours (NRS-worst pain, 0-10).\n\n-    MSKP-related illness perceptions (Brief Illness Perception Questionnaire, BIPQ, 0-80).\n\n-    MSKP-management strategies (Brief Pain Coping Inventory-2:SWE Traditional Pain Management Strategies subscale, BPCI-2:SWE TPMS, 0-56).\n\n-    Psychological flexibility (BPCI-2:SWE Psychological Flexibility, PF-subscale, 0-77).\n\n-    Reassurance of the benign nature of MSKP (NRS-reassurance, 0-10).\n\n-    Self-reported physical activity levels in the preceding week (FASTA-score, 3-19).\n\n- Self-reported sitting time (hours per day, 0-16hrs).\n\n- Global rating of change scale (GRoC, -5 to +5).\n\nThe following baseline covariates were used to adjust the models.\n\nAge, biological sex, body-mass-index, highest educational level, comorbidities (yes/no), work status (working/not working), sickness absence (absent/not absent), pain duration (acute/chronic with 3-month cut-off), pain localisation (regional pain/widespread pain), time from baseline to consultation (days), healthcare consultations for presenting MSKP in preceding 3-months (yes/no), Örebro Musculoskeletal Pain Screening Questionnaire (ÖMPSQ) risk category (high >50 points or low ≤50), analgesic use (yes/no).\n\nLiU secure repository is a data repository that hosts research data which cannot be openly available for ethical or legal reasons. LiU secure repository is managed by Linköping University Library as a service to researchers at Linköping University (Sweden). For requests of access or further information, please contact datamanagement@liu.se"@en;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

