<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/ac7b07c39380a3b1fb2153803d35d1a9> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "runes"@en, "runestone"@en, "rune stone"@en, "rune-stone"@en, "runic inscription"@en, "runsten"@en, "runinskrift"@en, "Runverket"@en, "Runristandets dynamik"@en, "Södermanland"@en, "Sö 45"@en, "Sö 52"@en, "Sö 75"@en, "Sö 112"@en, "Sö 113"@en, "Sö 128"@en, "Sö 129"@en, "Sö 131"@en, "Sö 134"@en, "Sö 137"@en, "Sö143"@en, "Sö 149"@en, "Sö 160"@en, "Sö 161"@en, "Sö 162"@en, "Sö 163"@en, "Sö 164"@en, "Sö 165"@en, "Sö 166"@en, "Sö 184"@en, "Sö 205"@en, "Sö 206"@en, "Sö 207"@en, "Sö 208"@en, "Sö 211"@en, "Sö 307"@en, "Sö 319"@en, "Sö 333"@en, "Sö 360"@en, "Sö 367"@en, "Sö 370"@en, "Sö 371"@en, "Sö Fv1948;282"@en, "Sö Fv1973;189"@en, "Sö Fv1954;19"@en, "Sö 1954;20"@en, "runor"@en;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2024-06-17T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2024-08-20T00:00:00Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "3D-data Runstenar i Södermanland / Runestones in Södermanland\n3D data Runestones in Södermanland"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/EDUC>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__6303.
_:b0__6303 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/e0926778acd5f41c66a95651951abd92>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/ac7b07c39380a3b1fb2153803d35d1a9> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021001090>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "3D-scans of runestones in Södermanland. This dataset includes 3D-models of 11th century AD runestones 3D-scanned for a study within the research project Runristandets dynamik (2009-2014). The project focussed on analysis of the runic inscriptions and ornament, therefor only the inscription surfaces have been scanned. For some stones, this is the only option as they are inserted into church walls.\n\nThe signum Sö + number is an ID-code used in the record of runic inscriptions kept by Runverket at the Swedish National Heritage Board. The signum originates in the corpus publication Sveriges runinskrifter and other printed publications, and is used in most publications and web-based resources. It is the key to find further references on a specific runic inscription and the object carrying it.\n\nThe runestones were 3D-scanned using ATOS I from GOM, measuring volume 250x200x200mm, measuring point distance 0.25mm, and are here provided in STL-format."@en;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

